text: Debra O'Connor (born 4 July 1966) is a Trinidad and Tobago badminton player, born in Jamaica. She competed in women's singles at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. She was a record ten times winner of the Women's Singles event at the Carebaco Games Caribbean Regional Badminton Championships. (1983 - 1987, 1990, 1992-1993, & 1995-1996). She also won the Women's Doubles Carebaco event nine times for Trinidad & Tobago and the Mixed Doubles event 3 times (1983, 1986 & 1990). ==References== ==External links== * Category:1966 births Category:Living people Category:Trinidad and Tobago female badminton players Category:Olympic badminton players of Trinidad and Tobago Category:Badminton players at the 1996 Summer Olympics
